vuln-patch-agent (MVP)
======================

This package provides a CLI-based vulnerability discovery and selective patch
agent for Ubuntu 22.04.

Installed files
---------------
- /usr/bin/vuln-patch-agent
- /usr/lib/vuln-patch-agent/patch_agent.py
- /etc/vuln-patch-agent/config.json

Post-install behavior
---------------------
- Creates a non-login service account: patch-agent
- Creates runtime directories:
  - /var/lib/vuln-patch-agent
  - /var/log/vuln-patch-agent
- Installs selective sudo policy in /etc/sudoers.d/patch-agent:
  - apt-get update
  - apt-get install --only-upgrade *
- Initializes SQLite DB schema.

Typical commands
----------------
Note: Runtime directories are owned by the non-login service account
`patch-agent` (mode 0750). Run commands as root (e.g. via sudo) or as the
service account.

As root (recommended for interactive admin use)
------------------------------------------------
sudo vuln-patch-agent init-db
sudo vuln-patch-agent sync-nvd --max-pages 1
sudo vuln-patch-agent scan
sudo vuln-patch-agent patch --dry-run
sudo vuln-patch-agent report

As patch-agent (recommended for automated/service use)
-----------------------------------------------------
sudo runuser -u patch-agent -- vuln-patch-agent init-db
sudo runuser -u patch-agent -- vuln-patch-agent sync-nvd --max-pages 1
sudo runuser -u patch-agent -- vuln-patch-agent scan
sudo runuser -u patch-agent -- vuln-patch-agent patch --dry-run
sudo runuser -u patch-agent -- vuln-patch-agent report
